comments.comment:
I found a workaround, but it would be nice if this problem could be solved more elegantly.<br/>
<br/>
Since the file was being downloaded in its entirety, I added some code to ignore the EOFException.<br/>
<br/>
if (responseCode == HttpStatus.SC_OK &amp;&amp; entity != null) {<br/>
					outStream = new BufferedOutputStream(new FileOutputStream(outFilename));<br/>
					long length = entity.getContentLength();<br/>
					try {<br/>
						entity.writeTo(outStream);<br/>
					} catch (EOFException e) {<br/>
						// Sometimes we get EOFExceptions if the content length<br/>
						// wasn&#39;t specified by the server.  Ignore these but report<br/>
						// those where the content length was specified.<br/>
						if (length &gt;= 0) {<br/>
							throw e;<br/>
						}<br/>
					}<br/>
				}
